channel.title: LapTop Trouble.....Again
channel.description:
Ok, well on my laptop, whenever I try to connect to my wireless internet I get this error message in these exact words:
[b]ERROR[/b]
[b]The requested URL could not be retrieved[/b] __________________________________________________________________
While trying to retrieve the URL: http://moparisthebest.com/smf
The following error was encountered:
[ul][li][b]Access Denied.[/b][/li][/ul]
Access control configuration prevents your request from being allowed at this time. Please contact your service provider if you feel this is incorrect.
Your cache administrator is Support@uk.uu.net ________________________________________________________ Generated Wed, 28 Jun 2006 15:32:35 GMT by webcache00.Ind.ops.eu.uu.net (Squid/2.5.STABLE12)
This happened when I was trying to install a proxy a few months ago. I never got the internet working again. I broswed Google and found that others had this problem but they had installed Squid, which is a proxy. I have no idea how to get rid of Squid as it is not in my "Add or Remove Programmes" or in any other place. Any ideas?
Many many many thanks to anyone that helps :)
